DataElement.preferredDefinition: Text term to describe the time of onset of nausea.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Nausea is the sensation of unease and discomfort from the stomach, with the sufferer feeling that he is about to vomit. (from Wikipedia)

Concepts.definition: Upper abdominal discomfort associated with an urge to vomit.

Property.preferredDefinition: Present; the period of time that is happening now.

Concepts.definition: Being or existing in a specified place or at the specified time.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition:
any unfavorable symptoms, signs, or disease temporally associated with the use of a medical
treatment or procedure that may or may not be considered related to the medical
treatment or procedure.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: Subjective evidence of disease perceived by the patient._The start, beginning, or early stages._The continuum of experience in which events pass from the future through the present to the past.
